I researched different ways to build the physical frame. Most builds use either wood or 3D-printed parts. I compared both and learned that 3D Printing allows for built-in cable channels, while wood is cheaper but harder to route wires through. I also looked at how other makers designed their frames aand how they mounted acrylic panels. Some people made it without any frame at all, but I thought this looked  tacky and unprofessional.

